			    STPJS 198</div>
  <p class="cont">in the heavens,<span class="footRef">1</span> and gave them their laws, conditions and bounds,<span class="footRef">2</span> which they cannot pass,<span class="footRef">3</span> except
  by His commandments; they all move in perfect harmony in their sphere and order,<span class="footRef">4</span> and are as
  lights, wonders and signs unto us.<span class="footRef">5</span> The sea also has its bounds<span class="footRef">6</span> which it cannot pass.<span class="footRef">7</span> God has set
  many signs on the earth,<span class="footRef">8</span> as well as in the heavens; for instance, the oak of the forest,<span class="footRef">9</span> the fruit of
  the tree,<span class="footRef">10</span> the herb of the field,<span class="footRef">11</span> all bear a sign that seed hath been planted there; for it is a decree
  of the Lord<span class="footRef">12</span> that every tree, plant, and herb bearing seed should bring forth of its kind,<span class="footRef">13</span> and cannot
  come forth after any other law or principle.<span class="textFootRef">a</span> Upon the same principle do I contend that baptism is
  a sign ordained of God, for the believer in Christ to take upon himself in order to enter into the
  kingdom of God, &ldquo;for except ye are born of water and of the Spirit ye cannot enter into the Kingdom
  of God,&rdquo;<span class="footRef">14</span> said the Savior. It is a sign and a commandment which God has set for man to enter into
  His kingdom. Those who seek to enter in any other way<span class="footRef">15</span> will seek in vain; for God will not receive
  them,<span class="footRef">16</span> neither will the angels acknowledge their works as accepted,<span class="footRef">17</span> for they have not obeyed the
  ordinances,<span class="footRef">18</span> nor attended to the signs which God ordained for the salvation of man, to prepare<span class="footRef">19</span> him
  for, and give him a title to, a celestial glory;<span class="footRef">20</span> and God had decreed that all who will not obey His
  voice<span class="footRef">21</span> shall not escape the damnation of hell.<span class="footRef">22</span> What is the damnation of hell? To go with that
  society who have not obeyed His commands.<span class="footRef">23</span></p>
  <div class="topic">Baptism and the Gift of the Holy Ghost</div>
  <p class="std">Baptism is a sign to God, to angels, and to heaven that we do the will of God,<span class="footRef">24</span> and there is no
  other way<span class="footRef">25</span> beneath the heavens<span class="footRef">26</span> whereby God hath ordained for man to come to Him to be saved,<span class="footRef">27</span>
  and enter into the Kingdom of God, except faith in Jesus Christ, repentance, and baptism for the
  remission of sins, and any other course is in vain;<span class="footRef">28</span> then you have the promise of the gift of the Holy
  Ghost.<span class="footRef">29</span></p>
  <p class="std">What is the sign of the healing of the sick? The laying on of hands is the sign or way marked
  out by James,<span class="footRef">30</span> and the custom of the ancient Saints as ordered by the Lord, and we</p>
